"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The heatmap function requires a 2D dataset that can be coerced into an ndarray. The pivot_table method creates a DataFrame that may not have the correct shape or values for a heatmap if the resulting DataFrame is empty or does not contain the expected data. In this case, dropping 'total_bill' and other categorical columns may lead to an incorrect or empty pivot table.\", \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< tips_new = tips.drop(['sex', 'smoker', 'time','total_bill'], axis=1)\\n---\\n> tips_new = tips[['day', 'size', 'tip']]\"}"